The paper discusses a tool for creating composite RDF resources from disparate sources, which involves data integration and consistency checks. This falls under the scope of database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves knowledge representation and reasoning. The paper also mentions Shape Expressions (ShEx) which is a language for describing RDF graph structures, indicating a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Empusa for generating Markdown documentation to make persistent URLs resolvable, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and deep learning (cs.DL) as these fields often involve natural language processing and text generation.
